product_name: freshBlack Tea Anti-Aging Moisturizer with Retinol-Alternative BT Matrix
summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsSustainable PackagingGive BackBlack Tea Anti-Aging Moisturizer with Retinol-Alternative BT Matrix from Fresh is a lightweight anti-aging cream with proven retinol-like performance.* *Ex vivo studies on BT Matrix ingredients; this product does not contain retinol.
details: DetailsBenefitsVisibly reduces deep set wrinklesVisibly improves skin's firmnessIncreases skin's radianceKey IngredientsBT MatrixTMA lightweight anti-aging cream with retinol-like performance* of BT Matrix for 7x smoother wrinkles, 5x visibly firmer skin & 4x more radianceCeramide NP is a skin-mimicking lipid produced using biotechnology that helps to strengthen the skin barrier, preventing moisture loss and dehydration.Pink porcelain lily is a smoothing leaf extract that improves skin texture and radiance by helping support the structure of the epidermis.Squalane helps to protect the skin and prevent moisture loss.Research Results7x visibly smoother wrinkles observed after 8 weeks*5x visibly firmer skin observed after 8 weeks*4x more radiance observed after 8 weeks*-31% look of deep wrinkles observed after 4 weeks**+64% visibly firmer skin observed after 4 weeks**+61% increased radiance observed after 4 weeks**+154% skin nourishment in just one use****Observed results, self-assessment by scoring, 29 subjects, comparing results from 1st application to after 8 weeks **observed results, self-assessment by scoring, 30 subjects, 4 weeks ***instrumental test, 32 subjectsItem 2603047How To UseApply to the face and neck daily, morning and night.IngredientsAqua (water), Glycerin, Pentylene Glycol, Cocoglycerides, Squalane, Glyceryl Stearate Citrate, Hydrogenated Coco-glycerides, Jojoba Esters, Propanediol, Polyglycerin-3, Camellia Sinensis Leaf Extract, Nephelium Lappaceum Leaf Extract, Alpinia Speciosa Leaf Extract, Tocopherol, Tocopheryl Acetate, Ceramide Np, Carbomer, Adenosine, Hydroxyacetophenone, Chlorphenesin, Sodium Hydroxide, Sodium Polyacrylate, Maltodextrin, Parfum (fragrance), Linalool, Citronellol, Geraniol \<17327\>.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Apply to the face and neck daily, morning and night.

reviews.headline: People have been telling me my skin is glowing
reviews.comments: My skin is glowing ever since I added this cream into my regimen.

reviews.headline: 2nd bottle
reviews.comments: Best face location I have come across. A bit pricey, but well worth it. It's not thick, and doesn't leave a residue. My face feels silky smooth and glowing.

reviews.headline: Great introductory product but not for 30+
reviews.comments:
I loved this when I was 25, it was lightweight and made my drylines disappear after a long night or studying/going out. 
Using it at the age of 30, it is lacking the strength needed for my skin personally.

reviews.headline: Beautiful glow
reviews.comments: I bought this for my mom who is in her 70s. This is exactly what she needed for dull, dry skin. We noticed that her wrinkles looked smoother after a few uses and what a healthy glow. Will buy again.

reviews.headline: Drying
reviews.comments: The cream never settled into the skin and made my skin feel dryer. Also, makeup did not apply nicely after it was on.

reviews.headline: Smells like pickles
reviews.comments: At first i liked it, but this product is extremely overpriced. I didnt notice a difference in my skin and it started to smell awful after a month

reviews.headline: RUN ( don't walk) to get this
reviews.comments: Hands up the best moisturizer for dry, aging skin. Incredible all-around.

reviews.headline: Makes my eyes burn
reviews.comments:
I did a ton of research snd was super excited to try this eye cream. I have very dark circles around my eyes and I was thinking this product would help with that. Unfortunately when i put it on, it makes the skin around my eyes buuuurrrrn. My eyes also arent that much more moisturized for such a thick cream. If you have sensetive skin, dont buy, its burns and is too expensive to try. 

Also, the deeper i dug, the more reviews i found that were written by people who were traded the product for free in return for a product review. Should have done more research….

reviews.headline: Love this product
reviews.comments: It makes my skin feel so soft, without being greasy at all, and makeup easily goes on over it. Only a small amount goes a long way

reviews.headline: Can't live without it!
reviews.comments: I am in love with this line, specifically this face cream and the eye cream. I have gone through two jars so far. I also use it on my neck and have noticed more of a difference there than on my face regarding tightening of skin. The cream is fairly light on the skin and is deeply hydrating. I ran out for a week and noticed an immediate difference! It can be a little shiny when combined with sunscreen and makeup however at night it just makes my skin glow. I am 48 and starting to battle some hormonal acne around my chin and mouth area so I have to avoid putting the cream around those areas. If I cant help myself (because it feels so good) I just get a few microscopic whiteheads that go away by the next day.

reviews.headline: Love it!
reviews.comments: I love this cream. It feels so smooth. Going on. Has a beautiful texture. I noticed my skin is very vibrant after I use it.

reviews.headline: Unfortunately.. I love it
reviews.comments: This is so good! I went out on a whim and bought it and im glad i did. My skin really likes it, and even though my skin usually hates new products, its stayed clear with this! The smell is nice and spa-like and it's a pleasant experience using it. It's very hydrating too! Can't speak much for wrinkles but it makes my skin look healthier!

reviews.headline: Not what I expected
reviews.comments: For the price point, I was disappointed in the moisture this product provided. I only purchased it to try it out because it was on sale but I would not repurchase and I would not buy full price. It also smells weird, I know fresh typically uses fragrance in their products but it doesn't smell great.

reviews.headline: Fresh , not greasy yet moiterizing
reviews.comments: I''ve used this cream for 2 weeks and think it's a keeper.

reviews.headline: Bad smell
reviews.comments: I havent used it long enough to know if it works. The smell is so offputting i dont want to use it

reviews.headline: Just started Using it
reviews.comments: The product has a very nice consistency and feels great on my face.  It is too soon to tell if it makes a difference but I really like it so far

reviews.headline: It's okay
reviews.comments: I have been using for about 2 weeks now 4 times a week and I am not super in love. Its keeps me moisturized but its no different than a Olay product for half the cost.

reviews.headline: Smoothing, Brightening, and Tightening. Worth every penny!
reviews.comments: I'm in love! after just 1 week of using this, my almost 45 year old skin has never looked better. It took a day or 2 for my skin to adjust to it. Was a little itchy at first but that has gone away. I can actually FEEL my skin tightening up and feel the quenching. I can't wait to use it every day. Amazing!

faceoff_positive.comments: I'm in love!!!!!!!! My 45 year old skin has never glowed like this, not even when I was in my 20's. After just 1 week of using it, I noticed a huge difference. My skin is brighter, tighter, and toned. My dark and red spots are disappearing. I've actually had strangers stop me in public and compliment my skin. It feels hydrating and smells amazing. It's even great on my sensitive skin. I would give this product 100 stars if I could. Worth every penny!!!
faceoff_positive.headline: Brightening, tightening, and smoothing!!!

faceoff_negative.comments: Zero stars! This cream is a terrible replacement that stung, irritated, itched, and does NOT moisturize nearly as wonderfully as the now gone Black Tea Age Delay Cream that I loved using for ~20 years. Hope they bring that formula back, and that they separate the reviews for the 2 products. The inclusion of those old reviews as though they apply to this new cream was very misleading. I am a decades-long Fresh-faithful (Milk lotion, age-delay creams, and sugar lip moisturizer) and hope they return to the pure ingredients that worked so well for so many.
faceoff_negative.headline: Stings, irritated, and did NOT moisturize
